column1: SVEDKA Blue Raspberry Vodka, 1 L Bottle, 70 Proof
column3: SVEDKA is an award-winning vodka made from the finest spring water and Swedish winter wheat, then distilled five times to remove impurities. Continuous distillation ensures that ingredients are constantly moving so the winter wheat, yeast, and water never stall or pool. With a pure, clear taste and crisp finish, dive in and discover full, bright berry flavors ending with a hard citrus crank with this delicious blend. It is smooth and easy drinking with a subtle, rounded sweetness that makes it perfect for mixing cocktails. Ideal for a Blue Heaven, SVEDKA Blue Raspberry has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: Black Velvet Reserve Canadian Whisky, 1.75 L Plastic Bottle, 80 Proof
column3: Black Velvet Reserve was started in 1991 and has steadily grown in popularity due to its smooth taste from longer aging. Black Velvet Reserve Canadian Whisky's smooth quality is the result of blending the whisky "at birth," meaning during maturation rather than later in the whisky-making process. Aged a minimum of eight years, this whisky features a nose of roasted nut, oak, chocolate, and pear, with slight spice, and peppery notes. Using crystal-clear Canadian water, plus the finest rye, grains, and corn, the whisky is painstakingly distilled and put up in premium oak barrels to gently mature. Ideal for any occasion, Black Velvet Whisky has a smooth texture that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes. The Black Velvet Distilling Company is located near the foothills of the Rocky Mountains in Lethbridge, Alberta, Canada.

column1: Black Velvet Reserve Canadian Whisky, 750 mL Bottle, 80 Proof
column3: Black Velvet Reserve was started in 1991 and has steadily grown in popularity due to its smooth taste from longer aging. Black Velvet Reserve Canadian Whisky's smooth quality is the result of blending the whisky "at birth," meaning during maturation rather than later in the whisky-making process. Aged a minimum of eight years, this whisky features a nose of roasted nut, oak, chocolate, and pear, with slight spice, and peppery notes. Using crystal-clear Canadian water, plus the finest rye, grains, and corn, the whisky is painstakingly distilled and put up in premium oak barrels to gently mature. Ideal for any occasion, Black Velvet Whisky has a smooth texture that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes. The Black Velvet Distilling Company is located near the foothills of the Rocky Mountains in Lethbridge, Alberta, Canada.

column3: SVEDKA is an award-winning vodka made from the finest spring water and Swedish winter wheat, then distilled five times to remove impurities. With a pure, clear taste and crisp finish, dive in and discover full, bright berry flavors ending with a hard citrus crank with this delicious blend. It is smooth and easy drinking with a subtle, rounded sweetness that makes it perfect for mixing cocktails. Ideal for a Blue Heaven, SVEDKA Blue Raspberry has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: Casa Noble Reposado Tequila, 750 mL Bottle, 80 Proof
column3: Casa Noble nurtures and harvests 100% Blue Weber agave in the rich, volcanic soil of Jalisco, Mexico for a consistently smooth flavor with unique characteristics and aromatic essences. Aromas of vanilla, lemongrass, and floral notes are balanced with flavors of sweet cooked agave and toasted oak in this smooth, sensuous, and full-bodied reposado tequila. These 80-proof fine tequilas are produced in small batches, triple distilled, and certified organic for ultra-premium, limited-run tequila that is truly one of a kind. This tequila is aged for 364 days in French white oak barrels compared to other reposados that are aged for four to six months. Ideal for a Margarita, Casa Noble Tequila has a balanced body that is a perfect addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: High West Double Rye Whiskey, 750 mL Bottle, 92 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West Double Rye! combines a young, spicy 2-year-old rye whiskey with a smooth 16-year-old for a spirited flavor with a caramel sweetness and woody vanilla richness to calm the "bite." This fine 92-proof whiskey blends straight ryes aged from 2 to 16 years in charred white oak barrels. The flavor features rye spices up front, then menthol, mint, eucalyptus, and herbal tea with wildflower honey underneath, gradually sweetening through the finish. Ideal for a Manhattan, High West whiskey has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: High West Rendezvous Rye Whiskey, 750 mL Bottle, 92 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879.  High West Rendezvous Rye Barrel Select Whiskey 92-proof is an extra aged, higher proofed, single barrel version of High West's standard Rendezvous Rye Whiskey. Traditional High West Rendezvous Rye whiskey blends older straight ryes aged from 5 to 19 years in charred white oak barrels, with the Barrel Select aged for 19 additional months. High West's flagship whiskey with a high rye content and uncompromised flavor.  The flavor is very spicy with notes of cinnamon, vanilla, caramel, molasses, and candied fruit. Ideal for a Manhattan, High West whiskey has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: High West Campfire Whiskey, 750 mL Bottle, 92 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. One taste of this sweet, spicy and, yes, smoky whiskey, and you’ll know how High West Campfire got its name. This fine 92-proof whiskey blends bourbon, rye, and peated scotch whiskey and is aged in white oak barrels as well as second-use bourbon barrels. It contains flavors of vanilla, honey, nutmeg, cinnamon, blueberries, and black cherries with a sweet, spicy, and smoky finish. Ideal for a Manhattan, High West whiskey has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: High West Silver Oat Whiskey, 750 mL Bottle, 80 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West Silver Western Oat Whiskey is an un-aged oat whiskey (akin to a blanco tequila) with a mash bill containing 85% oats and 15% barley malt. This 80-proof whiskey is a smooth oat-based whiskey that has just seen the inside of a barrel, with an elegant, smooth flavor. The flavor is light and sweet, tasting of cocoa and coconut infused character with a smooth vanilla finish. Ideal for wherever you'd use another clear spirit, High West Silver Whiskey is remarkably versatile.

column1: High West 7000 Vodka, 750 mL Bottle, 80 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West 7000 pays tribute to its high-altitude locale and its unique attributes, which lead to a great tasting vodka. This 80-proof vodka garners it's crisp, clear taste from natural grains that are filtered with natural snow-melt at an elevation of 7000 feet. This superb water is combined with carefully distilled oats to give High West 7000 its silky-smooth taste and rich mouthfeel. Best enjoyed where vodka is the primary ingredient, like neat, on the rocks, or in a Dry Martini.

column1: High West The 36th Vote Barreled Manhattan Whiskey, 750 mL Bottle, 74 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West created The 36th Vote Barreled Manhattan to commemorate Utah's role in the repeal of Prohibition. This 74-proof Manhattan uses the pre-Prohibition recipe of two parts rye whiskey to one part sweet vermouth and two dashes of bitters. This Manhattan tastes of muddled dried fruit, vinous liquor, spicy rye whiskey, and chocolate covered cherry with a subtle spiced fruit and slightly sweet finish. Best enjoyed neat, on the rocks, or stirred and strained with an orange or lemon garnish.

column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West Double Rye! combines a young, spicy 2-year-old rye whiskey with a smooth 16-year-old for a spirited flavor with a caramel sweetness and woody vanilla richness to calm the "bite." This fine 92-proof whiskey blends straight ryes aged from 2 to 16 years in charred white oak barrels. The flavor features rye spices up front, then menthol, mint, eucalyptus, and herbal tea with wildflower honey underneath, gradually sweetening through the finish. Ideal for a Manhattan, High West whiskey has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West American Prairie Bourbon is a complex blend of straight bourbons, producing an aromatic whiskey that helps preserve the West. High West American Prairie whiskey is rich and earthy on the palate. This fine 92-proof whiskey blends straight bourbons aged from two to 13 years in charred white oak barrels, making it a great sipper and a thoughtful person’s whiskey. Ideal for a Manhattan, High West whiskey has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: High West Valley Tan Whiskey, 750 mL Bottle, 87 Proof
column3: High West is Utah’s first distillery, born in 1879. High West Valley Tan Whiskey is a nod to the whiskey originally produced by the Mormon pioneers, made from a blend of wheat and oat whiskey. Valley Tan Whiskey is made from wheat and aged  in new and used barrels for a minimum of one year, creating a pretty sipping whiskey. This fine 87-proof whiskey tastes of crisp green apple, ripe honeydew melon, and jackfruit with a subtle white cake icing throughout and a clean finish featuring passion fruit and subtle pineapple. Best enjoyed anyway you like, on ice, with a little water, or even “squar” meaning neat or without water.

column1: SVEDKA Rose Vodka, 50 mL Plastic Bottle, 60 Proof
column3: SVEDKA is an award-winning vodka made from the finest spring water and Swedish winter wheat, then distilled five times to remove impurities. Continuous distillation ensures that ingredients are constantly moving so the winter wheat, yeast, and water never stall or pool. Blended with 5% rose wine, this 60-proof vodka is sweet and balanced with vibrant fruit aromas. Mouthwatering flavors of strawberry and pineapple complemented by notes of hibiscus and rose wine. It is smooth and easy drinking with a subtle, rounded sweetness that makes it perfect for mixing cocktails. Enjoy over the rocks with a splash of sparkling water, SVEDKA Rose has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.

column1: Mi Campo Reposado Tequila, 1 L Bottle, 80 Proof
column3: Mi Campo Reposado is crafted using high quality agave and tequila production methods to bring you a contemporary take on tequila. Made from 100% blue weber agave, the pinas are squeezed not crushed, then cooked in stone ovens. Our tequila is double distilled in alembic stills, and then rested three weeks in French oak barrels (70% pinot noir, 30% cabernet sauvignon) for aging. This 80-proof tequila is a light straw color with hints of gold sparkle. Aromas of cooked agave, ripe banana, apple, chocolate and cappuccino, layered over aromas of vanilla, cinnamon, pumpkin and clove. On the palate, honey maple, peaches and cream, white chocolate and a thread of minerality segues to a pepper and toasted oak finish.

Continuous distillation ensures that ingredients are constantly moving so the winter wheat, yeast, and water never stall or pool. Blended with 5% rose wine, this 60-proof vodka is sweet and balanced with vibrant fruit aromas. Mouthwatering flavors of strawberry and pineapple complemented by notes of hibiscus and rose wine. It is smooth and easy drinking with a subtle, rounded sweetness that makes it perfect for mixing cocktails. Enjoy over the rocks with a splash of sparkling water, SVEDKA Rose has a balanced body that is an ideal addition to countless cocktail recipes.
